info.title: Process Warehouse Tasks - Read, Update (A2X)
info.description:
In every API call, you can  make use of the following operations:
 - You can  retrieve warehouse orders and warehouse tasks. Apply  any of the filters provided or retrieve all existing data.
  - For existing warehouse orders, you can update the  corresponding warehouse tasks.
 - You can update  existing warehouse tasks (confirm, confirm with  exceptions, cancel).
 - You can update existing  warehouse orders (assign or unassign warehouse  order to warehouse resource).

x-sap-shortText: You can use this service to integrate external applications with warehouse orders and warehouse tasks in SAP S/4HANA Cloud

Alphanumeric key that identifies a complex, physical warehouse within the warehouse management system.  
All activities within a warehouse, for example, goods movements and physical inventory, are assigned to a specific warehouse number. The physical warehouse where these activities take place is identified by the warehouse number.

parameters.name: WarehouseTaskItem
parameters.description:
Warehouse Task Item  
Uniquely identifes a movement within a warehouse task (WT)  
Every WT item moves a product in a particular attribute and quantity from a storage bin (possibly cross-storage type) to a different storage bin (and if necessary, a remaining quantity to a third storage bin).

ConfirmationUTCDateTime.title: Time Stamp
ConfirmationUTCDateTime.description:
UTC Time Stamp in Short Form (YYYYMMDDhhmmss)  
The UTC timestamp is the date and time relative to the UTC (Universal coordinated time).  
To normalize local times in a UTC time stamp and make them comparable, they must be converted using their time zone and the ABAP command convert.Although the time zone for the conversion can be fetched from customizing or master data, you should save it redundantly.The internal structure of the UTC time stamp is logically divided into a date and time part in packed number format <YYYYMMDDhhmmss>. There is also a high resolution UTC time stamp (10^-7 seconds).

WhseTaskGoodsReceiptDateTime.description:

Specifies the date and time of the goods receipt of a product.

SeeTask-Oriented InstructionsReference Documentation for Semantic Properties of Domains

WarehouseProcessType.title: Whse Process Type
WarehouseProcessType.description:
Warehouse Process Type  
The system processes each warehouse process (such as goods receipt, goods issue, posting change, and repacking) using a warehouse process type. The warehouse process type has various effects on the creation of warehouse tasks.

ProductName.title: Product
ProductName.description:
Product Number  
Alphanumeric key uniquely identifying the product.

ProductDescription.title: Product Description
ProductDescription.description:
Text containing up to 40 characters that describes the product in detail.  
You can enter one product description in each of any number of languages.In principle, you enter the product description on the data screen of the first user department for which you enter data, and in your logon language. You can overwrite the product description on the Basic Data screen.

BatchChangeIsNotAllowed.title: Change Batch
BatchChangeIsNotAllowed.description: Changing the Batch is not Allowed

EntitledToDisposeParty.title: Disposal Party
EntitledToDisposeParty.description:
Party Entitled to Dispose  
An organization, defined as a business partner, that is entitled to dispose of stock. Usually this is the plant in which the stocks are planned, and in which the ATP check is performed.  
Each stock in the warehouse must be assigned to a party entitled to dispose.For each plant, there is exactly one partner master record with plant assignment in the vendor partner role.

ExecutingResource.title: Resource
ExecutingResource.description: Executing Resource (Means of Transport or User)

ProductionSupplyArea.title: Supply Area
ProductionSupplyArea.description:
Production Supply Area  
Defines the location that is used to stage products for use in production.  
The production supply area (PSA) is assigned to a warehouse number. You can also define bins within a PSA or common bins for multiple PSAs. When a delivery for production supply is being processed, the system assigns the bin to a product and a party entitled to dispose for the staging in the PSA.

PurchasingDocument.title: Purchasing Document
PurchasingDocument.description:
Purchasing Document Number  
Alphanumeric key uniquely identifying the document.

PurchasingDocumentItem.title: Item
PurchasingDocumentItem.description:
Item Number of Purchasing Document  
Specifies the number that uniquely identifies an item in .

SalesDocument.title: SD Document
SalesDocument.description:
Sales and Distribution Document Number  
The number that uniquely identifies the sales, delivery, or billing document.

SalesDocumentItem.title: Sales Document Item
SalesDocumentItem.description: The number that uniquely identifies the item in the sales document.

AlternativeUnit.title: Alt. Unit of Measure
AlternativeUnit.description:
Alternative Unit of Measure for Stockkeeping Unit  
Unit of measure that you can use to enter quantities as an alternative to the base unit of measure.

TargetQuantityInBaseUnit.title: Target Quantity Base
TargetQuantityInBaseUnit.description:
Target Quantity in Base Unit of Measure  
Target quantity in stockkeeping unit that is being removed from the source storage bin.

TargetQuantityInAltvUnit.title: Target Quantity Altn
TargetQuantityInAltvUnit.description:
Target Quantity in Alternative Unit of Measure  
Target quantity in alternative unit of measure that is to be removed from the source storage bin.

WhseTaskNetWeightUnitOfMeasure.title: Weight Unit
WhseTaskNetWeightUnitOfMeasure.description: The weight unit is used, for example, for the maximum allowed weight and the weight of products in storage bins.

WhseTaskNetVolumeUnitOfMeasure.title: Volume Unit
WhseTaskNetVolumeUnitOfMeasure.description: The volume unit is used, for example, for the maximum allowed volume and the volume of products in storage bins.

SourceStorageType.title: Source Storage Type
SourceStorageType.description: Storage type from where the product to be transported is removed from storage.

SourceStorageSection.title: Source Stor. Section
SourceStorageSection.description:
Source Storage Section  
Storage section of the storage bin from where the material to be transferred is to be or was removed<.

SourceStorageBin.title: Source Storage Bin
SourceStorageBin.description: Storage bin from where the product to be transferred is removed.

DestinationStorageSection.title: Dest. Stor. Section
DestinationStorageSection.description:
Destination Storage Section  
Storage section of storage bin to which the product is to be put away or is being put away.

DestinationStorageBin.title: Destination Bin
DestinationStorageBin.description:
Destination Storage Bin  
Storage bin into which the product is put away.

DestinationResource.title: Dest.Resource
DestinationResource.description: Destination Resource (Means of Transport or User)

DestinationHandlingUnit.title: Dest. HU

Destination Handling Unit

ProductionSupplyArea.title: Supply Area
ProductionSupplyArea.description:
Production Supply Area  
Defines the location that is used to stage products for use in production.  
The production supply area (PSA) is assigned to a warehouse number. You can also define bins within a PSA or common bins for multiple PSAs. When a delivery for production supply is being processed, the system assigns the bin to a product and a party entitled to dispose for the staging in the PSA.

ConfirmationUTCDateTime.title: Time Stamp
ConfirmationUTCDateTime.description:
UTC Time Stamp in Short Form (YYYYMMDDhhmmss)  
The UTC timestamp is the date and time relative to the UTC (Universal coordinated time).  
To normalize local times in a UTC time stamp and make them comparable, they must be converted using their time zone and the ABAP command convert.Although the time zone for the conversion can be fetched from customizing or master data, you should save it redundantly.The internal structure of the UTC time stamp is logically divided into a date and time part in packed number format <YYYYMMDDhhmmss>. There is also a high resolution UTC time stamp (10^-7 seconds).

WarehouseProcessType.title: Whse Process Type
WarehouseProcessType.description:
Warehouse Process Type  
The system processes each warehouse process (such as goods receipt, goods issue, posting change, and repacking) using a warehouse process type. The warehouse process type has various effects on the creation of warehouse tasks.

ProductDescription.title: Product Description
ProductDescription.description:
Text containing up to 40 characters that describes the product in detail.  
You can enter one product description in each of any number of languages.In principle, you enter the product description on the data screen of the first user department for which you enter data, and in your logon language. You can overwrite the product description on the Basic Data screen.

EntitledToDisposeParty.title: Disposal Party
EntitledToDisposeParty.description:
Party Entitled to Dispose  
An organization, defined as a business partner, that is entitled to dispose of stock. Usually this is the plant in which the stocks are planned, and in which the ATP check is performed.  
Each stock in the warehouse must be assigned to a party entitled to dispose.For each plant, there is exactly one partner master record with plant assignment in the vendor partner role.

Warehouse.title: Warehouse Number
Warehouse.description:
Warehouse Number/Warehouse Complex  
Alphanumeric key that identifies a complex, physical warehouse within the warehouse management system.  
All activities within a warehouse, for example, goods movements and physical inventory, are assigned to a specific warehouse number. The physical warehouse where these activities take place is identified by the warehouse number.

WarehouseTask.title: Warehouse Task
WarehouseTask.description:
Number that uniquely identifies the warehouse task within a warehouse.  
All movements in a warehouse are processed in the system via warehouse tasks.

WarehouseTaskItem.title: WT Item
WarehouseTaskItem.description:
Warehouse Task Item  
Uniquely identifes a movement within a warehouse task (WT)  
Every WT item moves a product in a particular attribute and quantity from a storage bin (possibly cross-storage type) to a different storage bin (and if necessary, a remaining quantity to a third storage bin).

WarehouseTaskExceptionCode.title: Exception Code
